nmcCfgSystemTime.name: nmcCfgSystemTime
nmcCfgSystemTime.description: This parameter is used to set and read the current time as kept by the NMC's real-time clock. It should be set to the local time in the place where the chassis is physically located. The real-time clock has the capability of maintaining correct time for short durations without power.

nmcCfgSystemDate.name: nmcCfgSystemDate
nmcCfgSystemDate.description: This parameter is used to set and read the current date as kept by the NMC's real-time clock. It should be set to the local date where the chassis is physically located.

nmcGmtime.name: nmcGmtime
nmcGmtime.description: This object reflects the current time in Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). The value of this object is sent in USR's enterprise specific SNMP trap messages for use by the receiving Management Stations.

nmcTimezone.name: nmcTimezone
nmcTimezone.description: This object should be set to reflect the timezone in which the chassis is physically located. It is used in the conversion from local time to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). The timezones are named for the number of hours by which GMT differs from local time. Default=gmtPlus0(21).

nmcCfgAuthFailTrapEnable.name: nmcCfgAuthFailTrapEnable
nmcCfgAuthFailTrapEnable.description: This object indicates whether or not the SNMP Proxy Agent running in the Network Management Card is to send a trap upon reception of an SNMP message that was not properly authenticated. MIB-I and II require a mechanism for enabling/disabling generation of this trap.

nmcDaySavingTime.name: nmcDaySavingTime
nmcDaySavingTime.description: The value of this object determines whether or not the NMC will honor daylight savings time when converting from local time to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT).

nmcCfgWanDialOutPhoneNum.name: nmcCfgWanDialOutPhoneNum
nmcCfgWanDialOutPhoneNum.description: This is the phone number that the NMC will use to dial a modem that is connected to the WAN port if there is no existing connection when the NMC tries to send and IP datagram out that port.

nmcCfgAtString.name: nmcCfgAtString
nmcCfgAtString.description: This object is the user defined AT string that will be used to configure a modem connected to the NMC's WAN port if the NMC needs to dial out to make a connection.

nmcPowerUpAutoCfgEnable.name: nmcPowerUpAutoCfgEnable
nmcPowerUpAutoCfgEnable.description: This parameter defines whether or not to automatically configure cards when they are inserted into the chassis or when the chassis is powered on. If set to do the autoconfigure, the values used to configure the cards will be those that were last saved to the NMC's NVRAM. For cards that do not match the values in NVRAM, those cards will be configured with default values.

nmcCfgNumWanRetries.name: nmcCfgNumWanRetries
nmcCfgNumWanRetries.description: This will specify the number of attempts to be made by port_write_task() to send the packet out of the WAN port while doing a dial up connection. The default is 0 which means the number of retries is disabled and it will keep trying to transmit the same packet for ever until it succeeds.

nmcCfgWanRetryPause.name: nmcCfgWanRetryPause
nmcCfgWanRetryPause.description: The amount of time in seconds that the NMC will pause between attempts to transmit a packet. The default value for this object is 30.

nmcCfgWanRetrySuspendTime.name: nmcCfgWanRetrySuspendTime
nmcCfgWanRetrySuspendTime.description: The Time period in seconds for which the WAN port should suspend its attempts to send out the packet. This time period applies when the number of failures has reached a configured maximum. It may resume its retries after the time period.

nmcCfgNumFailBefSuspend.name: nmcCfgNumFailBefSuspend
nmcCfgNumFailBefSuspend.description: The number of connection failures to allow before suspending retries.

nmcCfgLogSrvrSelect.name: nmcCfgLogSrvrSelect
nmcCfgLogSrvrSelect.description: The server selection for event logging. Default=none(3).

nmcCfgLogPriSrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLogPriSrvrAddr
nmcCfgLogPriSrvrAddr.description: The primary logging server's IP address.

nmcCfgLogSecSrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLogSecSrvrAddr
nmcCfgLogSecSrvrAddr.description: The secondary logging server's IP address.

nmcCfgLogUdpPortNum.name: nmcCfgLogUdpPortNum
nmcCfgLogUdpPortNum.description: The logging server's UDP port number. Default=1646.

nmcCfgLogRetryCnt.name: nmcCfgLogRetryCnt
nmcCfgLogRetryCnt.description: The NMC logging client transmission retry count. Default=3.

nmcCfgLogCallStatGrpSel.name: nmcCfgLogCallStatGrpSel
nmcCfgLogCallStatGrpSel.description: The optional call statistics groups included in log messages. Groups are Usage(1), Data Transfer(2), Performance(3), Operating Mode(4) and RMMIE(5). Group 1 is always sent. Groups 2-5 are optional. Default = none(1).

nmcCfgLogMD5Calc.name: nmcCfgLogMD5Calc
nmcCfgLogMD5Calc.description: This Optional Object will indicate to the accounting Client whether to calculate MD5 for accounting request message or not. default=disable.

nmcCfgTFTPTimeout.name: nmcCfgTFTPTimeout
nmcCfgTFTPTimeout.description: This object will be used to set up the timeout for the TFTP retries. The default would be 12 sec and the maximum allowed timeout would be 30 sec.

nmcCfgDnsPriSrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgDnsPriSrvrAddr
nmcCfgDnsPriSrvrAddr.description: The primary DNS server's IP address.

nmcCfgDnsSecSrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgDnsSecSrvrAddr
nmcCfgDnsSecSrvrAddr.description: The secondary DNS server's IP address.

nmcCfgLog3SrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLog3SrvrAddr
nmcCfgLog3SrvrAddr.description: The third backup logging server IP address to use.

nmcCfgLog4SrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLog4SrvrAddr
nmcCfgLog4SrvrAddr.description: The fourth backup logging server IP address to use.

nmcCfgLog5SrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLog5SrvrAddr
nmcCfgLog5SrvrAddr.description: The fifth backup logging server IP address to use.

nmcCfgLog6SrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLog6SrvrAddr
nmcCfgLog6SrvrAddr.description: The sixth backup logging server IP address to use.

nmcCfgLog7SrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLog7SrvrAddr
nmcCfgLog7SrvrAddr.description: The seventh backup logging server IP address to use.

nmcCfgLog8SrvrAddr.name: nmcCfgLog8SrvrAddr
nmcCfgLog8SrvrAddr.description: The eighth backup logging server IP address to use.

nmcCfgLogSrvrName.name: nmcCfgLogSrvrName
nmcCfgLogSrvrName.description: The host name of the logging server. Used to resolve logging server IP addresses through DNS query requests from the resolver.

nmcCfgDnsRetryCnt.name: nmcCfgDnsRetryCnt
nmcCfgDnsRetryCnt.description: The maximum number of retries that will be attempted to query a DNS before trying the secondary DNS.

nmcCfgDnsUdpPortNum.name: nmcCfgDnsUdpPortNum
nmcCfgDnsUdpPortNum.description: The logging server's UDP port number. Default=53.

nmcCfgDnsSrvrSelect.name: nmcCfgDnsSrvrSelect
nmcCfgDnsSrvrSelect.description: The server selection for DNS. Default=none(1).

nmcCfgLogDnsEna.name: nmcCfgLogDnsEna
nmcCfgLogDnsEna.description: Indicates whether logging server host address DNS resolution is enabled or disabled. Disabled, the logging server addresses are taken from the log server address objects.

nmcCfgLogStatusInterval.name: nmcCfgLogStatusInterval
nmcCfgLogStatusInterval.description: This value defines the interval in seconds between Status-Server requests for a failed RADIUS Accounting server connection. Default=30.

nmcCfgDnsSrvrFailure.name: nmcCfgDnsSrvrFailure
nmcCfgDnsSrvrFailure.description: This value defines the failure reason for last failure of DNS resolver query.

nmcCfgLogSrvrFailure.name: nmcCfgLogSrvrFailure
nmcCfgLogSrvrFailure.description: This value defines the failure reason for the last failure of RADIUS accounting server access.

nmcCfgSessionIDNewFmt.name: nmcCfgSessionIDNewFmt
nmcCfgSessionIDNewFmt.description: This Object is used to Enable/Disable the New Session ID Format. Default is Disable.

nmcStatStatus.name: nmcStatStatus
nmcStatStatus.description: This object will indicate the general status or health of the Network Management Card.

nmcStatDramInstalled.name: nmcStatDramInstalled
nmcStatDramInstalled.description: This object indicates the amount of dynamic RAM currently installed on the Network Management Card. The units for this value are kilobytes.

nmcStatNVRAMInstalled.name: nmcStatNVRAMInstalled
nmcStatNVRAMInstalled.description: This object indicates the amount of non-volatile RAM currently installed on the Network Management Card. The units for this value are kilobytes.

nmcStatEventId.name: nmcStatEventId
nmcStatEventId.description: This value increments once for each network management event detected by the NMC. It is used to correlate SNMP traps with events that occured in the system.

nmcStatTemperature.name: nmcStatTemperature
nmcStatTemperature.description: This object reflects the current temperature in the NAS chassis, as detected by the NMC. The value of this object indicates the temperature in degree Celcius.

nmcStatPowerUpTstFailures.name: nmcStatPowerUpTstFailures
nmcStatPowerUpTstFailures.description: This object contains the number of power up tests which failed during the power up of the NMC card.

nmcStatPowerUpTstFailBMap.name: nmcStatPowerUpTstFailBMap
nmcStatPowerUpTstFailBMap.description: This object defines a bit map which contains a one in the postion that indicates a power up test failure. The number returned is an integer that represents which power up test(s) that have failed. (e.g. a return value of three would mean power up tests 1 & 2 failed since bits 00000011 in the least significant byte would be set.)

nmcStatTestResult.name: nmcStatTestResult
nmcStatTestResult.description: This object contains the bit mapped result of the request to perform a self test. A non zero value indicates that there has been one or more self test failures.

nmcStatCompSwVer.name: nmcStatCompSwVer
nmcStatCompSwVer.description: This object contains the software compatibility version.

nmcStatPktBusClkSrc.name: nmcStatPktBusClkSrc
nmcStatPktBusClkSrc.description: The source of the backplane packet bus clock.

nmcStatNmcPktBusClk.name: nmcStatNmcPktBusClk
nmcStatNmcPktBusClk.description: The NMC's packet bus clock status.

nmcStatRedLed.name: nmcStatRedLed
nmcStatRedLed.description: This Object will return the Reason why the Hub Status LED is RED.

nmcAuxIn1Sts.name: nmcAuxIn1Sts
nmcAuxIn1Sts.description: This Object shows status of Aux Input port1.

nmcAuxIn2Sts.name: nmcAuxIn2Sts
nmcAuxIn2Sts.description: This Object shows status of Aux Input port2.

nmcAuxOut1Sts.name: nmcAuxOut1Sts
nmcAuxOut1Sts.description: This Object shows status of Aux Output port1.

nmcAuxOut2Sts.name: nmcAuxOut2Sts
nmcAuxOut2Sts.description: This Object shows status of Aux Output port2.

nmcTrapSequenceNumber.name: nmcTrapSequenceNumber
nmcTrapSequenceNumber.description: This object increments every time a trap is generated by the NMC. This object is sent in the var-bind list of each trap and can be used by management stations to detect when a trap has been lost.

nmcTrapDestTable.name: nmcTrapDestTable
nmcTrapDestTable.description: This table defines the places to which traps are to be sent. These places may refer to management consoles, or other alarm collection processes.

nmcTrapDestEntry.name: nmcTrapDestEntry
nmcTrapDestEntry.description: There is an entry in this table for each destination to which the NMC is to send SNMP traps.

nmcTrapDestIP.name: nmcTrapDestIP
nmcTrapDestIP.description: This object identifies the IP address to be used for sending traps to the destination identified by nmcTrapDestDescr.

nmcTrapDestCommunity.name: nmcTrapDestCommunity
nmcTrapDestCommunity.description: This object identifies the community string to be used when sending traps to the destination identified by nmcTrapDestDescr.

nmcTrapDestDescr.name: nmcTrapDestDescr
nmcTrapDestDescr.description: This object contains a plain text description of the trap destination to which this entry pertains.

nmcArTrapId.name: nmcArTrapId
nmcArTrapId.description: A single user defined value can be configured through AutoResponse script MIB objects to be sent to the management stations when a NMC AutoResponse SNMP TRAP occurs.

nmcCmdMgtStationId.name: nmcCmdMgtStationId
nmcCmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with ds0CmdReqId and ds0CmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

nmcCmdReqId.name: nmcCmdReqId
nmcCmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command or test on this Network Management Card. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the value zero.

nmcCmdFunction.name: nmcCmdFunction
nmcCmdFunction.description: This object contains the value which decsribe the command which is being invoked.

nmcCmdForce.name: nmcCmdForce
nmcCmdForce.description: In some cases, the Network Managment Card may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect operations. In such cases, a command request with this object not present or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, this object can be set to force in a subsequent issue of the command to cause the command to be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

nmcCmdParam.name: nmcCmdParam
nmcCmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no additional parameters required.

nmcCmdResult.name: nmcCmdResult
nmcCmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command or test, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

nmcCmdCode.name: nmcCmdCode
nmcCmdCode.description: The value of this object upon command completion indicates a further description of what went wrong if the command was unsuccessful. In the case of tests, a bit mapped result of each of the sub-tests performed appears in the nmcStatTestResult object.

nmcHsDialInOutNamePrompt.name: nmcHsDialInOutNamePrompt
nmcHsDialInOutNamePrompt.description: This is the first prompt that appears when users establish a connection with a security modem. It should serve to identify the system and prompt users to enter their name.

nmcHsDialInOutPsswdPrompt.name: nmcHsDialInOutPsswdPrompt
nmcHsDialInOutPsswdPrompt.description: This prompt appears after a valid response has been made to the previous prompt (i.e., name string followed by CR/LF), and prompts users to enter their password.

nmcHsDialBackNamePrompt.name: nmcHsDialBackNamePrompt
nmcHsDialBackNamePrompt.description: This prompt only appears when users are configured for dial back security (to either a stored or entered number). It is also only issued when the Request Login Validation on Dial-Back field is enabled for the user in the RADIUS user database. This prompt should be different than the name prompt used when users first log into the system.

nmcHsDialBackPsswdPrompt.name: nmcHsDialBackPsswdPrompt
nmcHsDialBackPsswdPrompt.description: This prompt appears after a valid response to the prior prompt, and prompts users to enter their password.

nmcHsDialBackPhonePrompt.name: nmcHsDialBackPhonePrompt
nmcHsDialBackPhonePrompt.description: This prompt only appears if you have configured the user for dial back entered mode in the RADIUS user database. It prompts the user to enter the phone number at which the system can call them back.

nmcHsDialBackPendPrompt.name: nmcHsDialBackPendPrompt
nmcHsDialBackPendPrompt.description: This message only appears if you configure users for a dial back mode (to either a stored or entered number) in the RADIUS user database. It confirms to users that they have logged in successfully, and lets them know that the system has reserved a modem to call them back.

nmcHsMdmSelectPrompt.name: nmcHsMdmSelectPrompt
nmcHsMdmSelectPrompt.description: This message only appears if a user is configured for dial back in the RADIUS database and that this record has the Request Dial Back Modem Selection field enabled. The system displays a list of allowed dial back modems that have been entered for this user. Users must enter the number that appears on the menu next to their choice.

nmcHsLoginFailedMsg.name: nmcHsLoginFailedMsg
nmcHsLoginFailedMsg.description: This message appears when users fail to enter a valid name/password combination.

nmcHsPhoneRestrictPrompt.name: nmcHsPhoneRestrictPrompt
nmcHsPhoneRestrictPrompt.description: This message appears when users are prompted for a dial back phone number and the entered number violates the allowed numbers specified in the Call Restriction List.

nmcHsInvalidMdmSelecMsg.name: nmcHsInvalidMdmSelecMsg
nmcHsInvalidMdmSelecMsg.description: This message appears when users configured for dial back with the Request Dial-Back Modem Selection field enabled, select a modem to which they are not allowed access (as specified in the list of allowed Dial-Back modems).

nmcHsNoMdnsAvailMsg.name: nmcHsNoMdnsAvailMsg
nmcHsNoMdnsAvailMsg.description: This message appears when the system is unable to reserve a modem for dial-back that was either selected by the user or defined in it's list of Allowed Dial Back modems.

nmcHsConnectSuccessMsg.name: nmcHsConnectSuccessMsg
nmcHsConnectSuccessMsg.description: This message confirms that users have successfully compleated their login and may proceed with either their dial-in or dial-out call.

nmcHsNewPasswordPrompt.name: nmcHsNewPasswordPrompt
nmcHsNewPasswordPrompt.description: This prompt only appears when a users password has expired. It is issued once for the new password and then again for re-issue of the new password.

nmcHsChangePasswordMsg.name: nmcHsChangePasswordMsg
nmcHsChangePasswordMsg.description: This message appears during name/password authentication when the user's password has expired. This message is immediately followed by the enter new password prompt.

nmcHsPromptRspTimeout.name: nmcHsPromptRspTimeout
nmcHsPromptRspTimeout.description: This value represents the number of seconds in which users must respond to each prompt. Users failing to respond within the specified time are disconnected, and a Dial Security login failure trap is generated. Any login failures of this type also apply to the user blacklist function if a valid user name has been entered. This field takes precidence over the modem's inactivity timer during a security login. The default for this object is 30(seconds).

nmcHsPromptRspAttempts.name: nmcHsPromptRspAttempts
nmcHsPromptRspAttempts.description: This value represents the number of tries the user is allowed per prompt during any one security session. If this number is reached, the call is terminated. For the purposes of retry limiting, the user name and password are treated as a single prompt. This means that if a valid name and an invalid password are entered, the failure is counted against both the Prompt Response Attempt Limit and the Failed Logins Before Blacklist. The default for this object is 1.

nmcHsPromptRspEchoEna.name: nmcHsPromptRspEchoEna
nmcHsPromptRspEchoEna.description: When enabled, this option instructs the NMC to echo the user's typed responses back to the users screen. Password responses are echoed as 'X's. The default for this option is disabled.

nmcHsDialBackDelay.name: nmcHsDialBackDelay
nmcHsDialBackDelay.description: This object defines the number of seconds to wait between successive dial back attempts; i.e., the time the NMC waits before attempting the next dial back when it was unable to connect. The default is 30 seconds.

nmcHsDialBackAttempts.name: nmcHsDialBackAttempts
nmcHsDialBackAttempts.description: This object defines the number of times that the NMC will attempt to dial back a dial in user configured for dial back when successive dial back attempts fail. The default for this object is one.

nmcHsSecuritySrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecuritySrvrAddr
nmcHsSecuritySrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the Primary RADIUS security server where the NMC RADIUS client sends requests.

nmcHsSecuritySrvrPort.name: nmcHsSecuritySrvrPort
nmcHsSecuritySrvrPort.description: This object identifies the UDP port where the NMC's RADIUS client issues requests to the RADIUS security server. The default port is 1645.

nmcHsSecuritySrvrRetries.name: nmcHsSecuritySrvrRetries
nmcHsSecuritySrvrRetries.description: This object identifies the number of retries that the NMC's RADIUS client will preform when attempting to send requests to a RADIUS security server. The default retry number is 1.

nmcHsMdmAttemptLimit.name: nmcHsMdmAttemptLimit
nmcHsMdmAttemptLimit.description: This value represents the number of times an attempt can be made to login on any one modem without success. If this value is exceeded and the mdmLoginAttemptLimExceeded trap has been enabled, then the mdmLoginAttemptLimExceeded trap is generated. Default = 3.

nmcHsServerUnavailable.name: nmcHsServerUnavailable
nmcHsServerUnavailable.description: This option specifies whether to deny or allow a call when a dial security server is unreachable. Default = denyCall(1).

nmcHsServerSelect.name: nmcHsServerSelect
nmcHsServerSelect.description: Server Selection for RADIUS Security. Default=none(3).

nmcHsSecondarySrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecondarySrvrAddr
nmcHsSecondarySrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the Secondary RADIUS Security Server.

nmcHsDiPasswdEnaDis.name: nmcHsDiPasswdEnaDis
nmcHsDiPasswdEnaDis.description: This Optional Object will Enable/Disable PASSWORD prompt for Dial-In Hub Security. Default is Enable(1).

nmcHsSecurity3SrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecurity3SrvrAddr
nmcHsSecurity3SrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the 3rd RADIUS Security backup server.

nmcHsSecurity4SrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecurity4SrvrAddr
nmcHsSecurity4SrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the 4th RADIUS Security backup server.

nmcHsSecurity5SrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecurity5SrvrAddr
nmcHsSecurity5SrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the 5th RADIUS Security backup server.

nmcHsSecurity6SrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecurity6SrvrAddr
nmcHsSecurity6SrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the 6th RADIUS Security backup server.

nmcHsSecurity7SrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecurity7SrvrAddr
nmcHsSecurity7SrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the 7th RADIUS Security backup server.

nmcHsSecurity8SrvrAddr.name: nmcHsSecurity8SrvrAddr
nmcHsSecurity8SrvrAddr.description: This object identifies the IP address of the 8th RADIUS Security backup server.

nmcHsSecuritySrvrName.name: nmcHsSecuritySrvrName
nmcHsSecuritySrvrName.description: Identifies the host name of the RADIUS Security server used to resolve IP addresses through DNS queries.

nmcHsSecuritySrvrDnsEna.name: nmcHsSecuritySrvrDnsEna
nmcHsSecuritySrvrDnsEna.description: Indicates RADIUS Security server IP addresses are resolved through DNS queries. If disabled, the Security server address objects are used. Default=disabled

nmcHsSecurityStatusInt.name: nmcHsSecurityStatusInt
nmcHsSecurityStatusInt.description: This value defines the interval in seconds between Status-Server requests for a failed RADIUS Security server connection. Default=30.

nmcHsSecurityFailure.name: nmcHsSecurityFailure
nmcHsSecurityFailure.description: This value defines the failure reason for the last failure of RADIUS Security server access.

nmcTeDialOutLoginFail.name: nmcTeDialOutLoginFail
nmcTeDialOutLoginFail.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a dial out login security session has failed.

nmcTeDialInLoginFail.name: nmcTeDialInLoginFail
nmcTeDialInLoginFail.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a dial in login security session has failed.

nmcTeDialOutRestrictNum.name: nmcTeDialOutRestrictNum
nmcTeDialOutRestrictNum.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a dial out security session has failed as a result of attempting to dial a restricted phone number.

nmcTeDialBackRestrictNum.name: nmcTeDialBackRestrictNum
nmcTeDialBackRestrictNum.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a dial back security session has failed as a result of attempting to dial a restricted phone number.

nmcTeUserBlacklist.name: nmcTeUserBlacklist
nmcTeUserBlacklist.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a security user has reached their final failed login attempt number and is now being blacklisted.

nmcTeUserBlacklistLogin.name: nmcTeUserBlacklistLogin
nmcTeUserBlacklistLogin.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a security login attempt by a currently blacklisted user has occurred.

nmcTeRespAttmptLimExceed.name: nmcTeRespAttmptLimExceed
nmcTeRespAttmptLimExceed.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a security user has failed to issue a valid response to a particular security prompt before the configured limit.

nmcTeLoginAttmptLimExceed.name: nmcTeLoginAttmptLimExceed
nmcTeLoginAttmptLimExceed.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when a security session has failed because the indicated user does not appear in the security user database.

nmcTeLogSrvrLoss.name: nmcTeLogSrvrLoss
nmcTeLogSrvrLoss.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with a logging server has been lost.

nmcTeSecSrvrLoss.name: nmcTeSecSrvrLoss
nmcTeSecSrvrLoss.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with a security server has been lost.

nmcTeSinglePbClockFail.name: nmcTeSinglePbClockFail
nmcTeSinglePbClockFail.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when the NMC detects that there is a packet bus clock failure in a single slot. Default=enable(1).

nmcTePbClockSwitch.name: nmcTePbClockSwitch
nmcTePbClockSwitch.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when the NMC detects that there is a packet bus clock failure in multiple slots and the NMC has assumed the role of clock master. Default=enable(1).

nmcTePbClockFail.name: nmcTePbClockFail
nmcTePbClockFail.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when the NMC detects that the packet bus clock on the NMC daughter board pcb has failed. Check status of nmcStatPktBusClkSrc to determine if the NMC was acting as clock master. Default=enable(1).

nmcTeDnsSrvrLoss.name: nmcTeDnsSrvrLoss
nmcTeDnsSrvrLoss.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with the primary and secondary DNS server has been lost.

nmcTeNtpSrvrLoss.name: nmcTeNtpSrvrLoss
nmcTeNtpSrvrLoss.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with all NTP servers has failed.

nmcTeNtpSrvrRestore.name: nmcTeNtpSrvrRestore
nmcTeNtpSrvrRestore.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with the NTP server has been restored.

nmcTeNtpSrvrDegraded.name: nmcTeNtpSrvrDegraded
nmcTeNtpSrvrDegraded.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with the primary NTP server has failed, but the secondary has been restored.

nmcTeDnsSrvrRestore.name: nmcTeDnsSrvrRestore
nmcTeDnsSrvrRestore.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with the primary DNS server has been restored. Default=disable.

nmcTeDnsSrvrDegraded.name: nmcTeDnsSrvrDegraded
nmcTeDnsSrvrDegraded.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with the primary DNS server has failed, but the secondary DNS server is operational. Default=disabled.

nmcTeLogSrvrRestore.name: nmcTeLogSrvrRestore
nmcTeLogSrvrRestore.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with a logging server has been restored.

nmcTeLogSrvrGroupOper.name: nmcTeLogSrvrGroupOper
nmcTeLogSrvrGroupOper.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when the communication with the group of logging servers is operational with the primary server in service.

nmcTeLogSrvrGroupDegr.name: nmcTeLogSrvrGroupDegr
nmcTeLogSrvrGroupDegr.description: Enable/disable from the trap generated when the communication with the group of logging servers has degraded with a non-primary server in service.

nmcTeLogSrvrGroupNonOp.name: nmcTeLogSrvrGroupNonOp
nmcTeLogSrvrGroupNonOp.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when the communication with the group of logging servers is non-operational.

nmcTeSecSrvrRestore.name: nmcTeSecSrvrRestore
nmcTeSecSrvrRestore.description: Enable/disable for the trap generated when communication with the RADIUS Security server has been restored. Default=disabled

nmcTeSecSrvrGroupOper.name: nmcTeSecSrvrGroupOper
